unique:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr →* » -/
theorem to_group.unique (g : «expr →* » (presented_group rels) G) (hg : ∀ x : α, g (of x) = f x) :
    ∀ {x}, g x = to_group h x := fun x =>
  quotient_group.induction_on x fun _ => free_group.lift.unique (g.comp (quotient_group.mk' _)) hg
#align to_group.unique to_group.unique
to_group_eq_one_of_mem_closure:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprF -/
theorem to_group_eq_one_of_mem_closure : ∀ x ∈ subgroup.normal_closure rels, (exprF) x = 1 := fun x w =>
  (monoid_hom.mem_ker _).1 <| closure_rels_subset_ker h w
#align to_group_eq_one_of_mem_closure to_group_eq_one_of_mem_closure
of:
@[simp]
theorem to_group.of {x : α} : to_group h (of x) = f x :=
  free_group.lift.of
#align to_group.of to_group.of
closure_rels_subset_ker:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `exprF -/

/-
Presented groups satisfy a universal property. If `G` is a group and `f : α → G` is a map such that
the images of `f` satisfy all the given relations, then `f` extends uniquely to a group homomorphism
from `presented_group rels` to `G`.
-/
theorem closure_rels_subset_ker : subgroup.normal_closure rels ≤ monoid_hom.ker (exprF) :=
  subgroup.normal_closure_le_normal fun x w => (monoid_hom.mem_ker _).2 (h x w)
#align closure_rels_subset_ker closure_rels_subset_ker
